<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>History of the Environmental Sciences
Division</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><IMG
SRC="http://www.esd.ornl.gov/images/esdlogo-small.gif"> History of the
Environmental Sciences Division</H1>

<I>Robert V. O'Neill</I><P>

An anecdotal survey of the history of ESD from 1967 to 1995 was
presented by Robert V. O'Neill, an employee since 1967.  Since that
time, the Radiation Ecology Group, which had a staff of 12, has evolved
into the Environmental Sciences Division which currently has more than
200 staff members.  This rapid growth in environmental concerns forms
an important part of the history of ORNL.  The basic facilities,
scientific approaches, and technical expertise of the Division have
developed during this time.  An anecdotal history of this period, seen
from one employee's perspective, should help staff and committee members
understand the strength, spirit, and reputation of the present
organization.<P>

