<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Earth Sciences and ESD</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><IMG
SRC="http://www.esd.ornl.gov/images/esdlogo-small.gif"> Earth Sciences
and ESD</H1>

<I>Stephen H. Stow</I><P>

The importance of earth sciences to ESD and its predecessor
organizations was reviewed from the 1940s to the present.  Earth
sciences have been an essential part of the activities of ESD with an
emphasis on waste disposal issues and biogeochemistry.  The growth in
earth science staff (in relation to the life sciences staff) has been
steady and consistent since ESD was formed in 1972, although the
distinction between the earth sciences and the life sciences is often
difficult to make.  Many new opportunities exist for further
development of the earth (and engineering) sciences, but such
development will take perseverance and imagination.<P>

<HR>
<A HREF="stow.au"><IMG ALT="[Audio]" SRC="/images/sound.xbm"> Listen to Stow's talk</A>
<HR>

<H5><IMG SRC="stow1.gif"><br>
