from early earth sciences work at the Lab.</H5>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<I>STEPHEN (Steve) H. STOW received a B.A. from Vanderbilt University in
1962 and an M.A. and a Ph.D. from Rice University in 1965 and 1966,
respectively.  He worked at CONOCO before joining the faculty at the
University of Alabama, where he was Professor of Geology.  Steve joined
ESD in 1980 and is now Program Manager for the Division's Environmental
Management Program.  Since 1980, he served in various capacities,
including Program Manager for the Waste Isolation Program and the
Sedimentary Rock/Geoscience Technology Support programs, which dealt
with high-level nuclear waste disposal; manager for ORNL's Formerly
Utilized Sites Remedial Action Program; manager of the geotechnical
research aspects of ORNL's hydrofracture activities; and Section Head
for Earth and Atmospheric Sciences in ESD.  He is also active at the
national and international levels in environmental, geoscience, and
waste management activities and promotes science education initiatives
in many earth science societies.  Steve has published more than 50
pieces dealing with geosciences, waste management, and resource issues.</I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

