<HTML>
<HEAD>
<META NAME="keywords" CONTENT="biomass, bioenergy, biofuels">
<TITLE>Biofuels Feedstock Development Program</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#238E23" LINK="#008080" VLINK="#5c3317" ALINK="#000000">
<CENTER>
<H1><IMG
SRC="images/biologo.gif" ALT="Biofuels" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="85"><I>Biofuels
Feedstock Development Program</I></H1></CENTER>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="5">
<TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="10%">
<P>To contact the BFDP management team,
<A HREF="mgtteam2.html">click here</A> for the names, phone numbers, and email
addresses.</P>
</TD>
<TD>
<P>The <B><FONT SIZE="+1">U.S. Department of Energy's (DOE) Biofuels
Feedstock Development Program (BFDP)
</FONT></B> is a mission-oriented program of research and analysis whose goal is
to develop and demonstrate environmentally acceptable crops and cropping systems
for producing large quantities of low-cost, high-quality biomass feedstocks.
BFDP has screened more than 125 tree and nonwoody species and selected a limited
number of model species for development as energy crops. At least 30
universities, 5 U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) research units, and 4
private industries or businesses have been long-term (5 years or more)
participants in BFDP research. Many BFDP projects receive significant
cost-sharing from other public and private sources.
</P></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD>
<P>Our mailing address is
<BR><B>Biofuels Feedstock Development Program<BR> Oak Ridge National
Laboratory<BR> P.O. Box 2008, MS-6422 <BR> Oak Ridge, TN 37831-6422 USA</B></P></TD>
<TD>
<P> 
<A HREF="http://www.ornl.gov/"><B>Oak Ridge National Laboratory</B> </A>has
provided technical leadership and field management for BFDP since DOE began
energy crop research in 1978. The program now supports studies in 5 areas:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>Wood Energy Species
</LI>
<LI>Herbaceous Energy Species 
</LI>
<LI>Environmental Research
</LI>
<LI>Systems Integration and Analysis</LI>
<LI>Scale-Up, Feasibility, and Demonstration
</LI></UL>
<P><A HREF="doeofd/94_95sum/toc2.html#bfdptasks">Click here for information
about the projects and tasks currently being funded.</A></P></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD>
<P>BFDP researchers lead the nation in applying biotechnology to hardwood tree
species, including tissue culture propagation techniques, genetic
transformation, and genetic mapping. BFDP's crop development research is
complemented by resource assessments, economic analysis, and environmental
research and analysis that provide the information needed to demonstrate and
commercialize biomass energy systems.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<CENTER>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="5" WIDTH="400">
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/ecf_sm.gif" WIDTH="50" HEIGHT="50"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="80%"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B><A HREF="forum/ecftoc.html">Energy Crops
Forum Newsletter</A></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/b_librar.gif" ALT="Book icon" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="40"></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><B><A HREF="reports/repstoc.html">Biofuels Feedstock
Development Program Reports</A></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/bbook.gif"></TD>
<TD><A HREF="papers/pubtoc.html"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>BFDP Fact Sheets,
Articles, and White Papers</B></FONT></A></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/paper.gif" ALT="paper icon" WIDTH="33" HEIGHT="42"></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><B><A
HREF="http://www.esd.ornl.gov/cgi-bin/bfdp/report-index">BFDP Weekly Activity
Reports</A></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/b_librar.gif" ALT="Book icon" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="40"></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><B><A
HREF="http://dsimd.dsrd.ornl.gov/htmldocs/biofuels/biofuels.htp" NAME="bib">BIOBIB,
a searchable bibliographic database</A></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/tree.gif" ALT="tree icon" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32"></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="+1"><B><A HREF="srwcwgrp/menu.html">Short-Rotation Woody
Crops Operations Working Group</A></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>
