<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Maps</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#0000BB" TEXT="#FFFF00" LINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#CCCCCC">
<BASEFONT SIZE="4">
<H1>Maps</H1>

<HR>
<P>
Field sampling for biotic, toxicity, and chemical analysis was
performed between November 1993 and September 1994.  Three major
sampling efforts were performed during this time:  biota (fish and
benthic invertebrates), sediment and pore-water, and surface water.
The following is a set of maps depicting sampling location for subtasks
within each major sampling group.</P>
<HR>

<A NAME="study"><H2>Study Area</H2></A>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="SUBREACH.PS"> Study Areas</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
The Clinch River Study area includes Melton Hill and Watts Bar
Reservoirs which wrap around the Department of Energy's Oak Ridge
Reservation.  Study subreaches were created to delineate areas of
influence from major tributaries or changes in river structure.</P>

<LI> The River Mile Problem

<P><UL>
<LI> <A HREF="../DOCS/RIVERMI/P114.HTM">The Solution</A>
<LI> <A HREF="../DOCS/RIVERMI/P114F.GIF">Map of River Miles</A>
</UL></P>

</UL>

<HR>

<A NAME="biota"><H2>Biota</H2></A>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="BUGSITES.PS"> Sampling Locations for Benthic
Invertebrate Survey</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows were TVA collected benthic invertebrate samples to
determine community structure.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="FISH.PS"> Fish Sampling Locations</A> (Postscript, Ledger
Size)

<P>
This map shows where fish were collected to determine contaminant
concentrations in fish flesh and fish community structure.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="OSPREY.PS"> Osprey Nest in Poplar Creek</A>
(Postscript, Letter Size)

<P>
</P>

</UL>

<HR>

<A NAME="sediment"><H2>Sediment</H2></A>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="SEDTOX.PS">Sampling Locations for Sediment Toxicity
Task</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This is a map or sites where sediment and pore-water was collected to
perform toxicity tests with amphipods and mussels.  Contaminant
analysis and benthic invertebrate sampling was also conducted for these
sites.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="SEDIMENT.PS"> Sediment Sampling Locations for Task S1B</A>
(Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This is a map of sites where sediment and pore-water samples were
collected for organic, inorganic, radiological, and physical
analysis.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="RIVCS.GIF"> Average Cs-137 Concentrations with 1
mile intervals in Surface Sediments</A>

<P>
This map depicts the average Cs-137 concentration in surface sediments
for 1 mile intervals in the Clinch River Arm of Watts Bar Reservoir.
The data used for this representation are from <A
HREF="../DOCS/ER_264.HTM">Levine, et. al., 1994</A>.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="SOURCE.PS"> Sampling Locations for Source Area
Characterization Task</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows locations where TVA collected water and surface sediment
for screening level analysis.  The purpose of this task was to
determine if potential non-DOE sources were contributing contaminants
to the system.</P>

</UL>

<HR>

<A NAME="water"><H2>Water</H2></A>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="WATERTOX.PS"> Sampling Locations for Water Toxicity
Task</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows where water samples were collected to perform toxicity
tests with fathead minnows and daphnia.  Contaminant analysis were also
performed on water from these sites.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="BIASWATR.PS"> Sampling Locations for Biased-Event Water
Sampling</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows where water samples were collected during spring and
summer dry and wet periods.  The intent was to collect water during
extreme events because that is when the highest contaminant
concentration were expect. Samples were analyzed for organic,
inorganic, and radiological contaminants in filtered and un-filtered
samples. Water was collected from the surface and near the bottom at
each location.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="REMOBIL.PS"> Contaminant Remobilization Study Sampling
Locations</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows where water samples were collected 1 meter above the
sediment surface.  The intent of this tasks was to determine if
detectable quantities of contaminants were being release from the
sediment.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="WATER14.PS"> Sampling Locations for Plume Detection Task</A>
(Postscript, Letter Size)

<P>
This map shows where water samples were collected in transects below
suspected outfalls of contaminants in Poplar Creek.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="ORREM.PS"> Oak Ridge Reservation Environmental Monitoring
(ORREM) Sites</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
ORREM regularly collects water samples from sites depicted in this map,
among other sites.  Data from these sites were used in the overall
evaluation for water charaterization.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="SOURCE.PS"> Sampling Locations for Source Area
Characterization Task</A> (Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows locations where TVA collected water and surface sediment
for screening level analysis.  The purpose of this task was to
determine if potential non-DOE sources were contributing contaminants
to the system.</P>

</UL>

<HR>

<A NAME="historical"><H2>Historical Studies</H2></A>

<P>
A number of studies have been performed on Clinch River sediments over
the last 50 years.  <A HREF="../DOCS/REFS.HTM#Oakes-1982">Oakes, et.
al., 1982</A>, and <A HREF="../DOCS/REFS.HTM#Ashwood-1986">Ashwood, et.
al., 1986</A>, both had sufficient information to generate GIS data
bases and provide data for additional spatial analysis.</P>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="OAKES1.PS"> Oakes Cesium Sampling Locations</A>
(Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map shows the locations of sediment sample collection during the
Oakes et al 1982 study.  Sampling was restricted to water less than 15
feet deep due to equipment limitations therefore samples appear to be
pushed towards the shoreline. These sediment samples were analyzed by
gamma-spectroscopy to determine Cs-137 concentrations in
particular.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="OAKES2.PS"> Oakes Cesium Sampling - Depth-to-Peak</A>
(Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map portrays, in relative scale, the depth to highest
concentration of Cs-137 in each core.  The Cs-137 concentration peak is
associated with peak releases from White Oak Lake in the late 50s.
Shallow peaks indicate that sediment deposition rates are low or that
scouring is occuring.  Deep peaks indicates relatively high deposition
rates.  Note the high variability within adjacent cores.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="OAKES3.PS"> Oakes Cesium Sampling - Total Cesium</A>
(Postscript, Ledger Size)

<P>
This map portrays, in a relative scale, the total Cs-137 at each sample
location.</P>

<LI> <A HREF="ASHWOOD.PS"> Ashwood Sampling Locations</A>
(Postscript, Letter Size)

<P>
This map depicts sampling locations for surface sediment samples
collected by <A HREF="../DOCS/REFS.HTM#Ashwood-1986">Ashwood, et. al.,
1986</A>.  The purpose of this project was to sample along the exposed
shorelines and in the tributaries of Poplar Creek and the Clinch River
surrounding K-25 to determine where concentrations of contaminants are
highest.  This data were incorporated into the GIS and, in conjuction
with the Phase 2 sediment data, have been useful in identifying sources
of various contaminants.</P>

</UL>

