<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Differential Post-Processing GPS Data Using the
Ashtech Ranger Software</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="IMAGES/YWEAVE.GIF">
<BASEFONT SIZE="4">
<CENTER><H1>Differential Post-Processing GPS Data Using the Ashtech Ranger
Software</H1></CENTER>

<OL>
<LI>Enter the <CODE>RANGER</CODE> program on your computer.<P>

<LI>Once in the main menu, type <KBD>B</KBD> or tab to
<SAMP>B) Differential Processing</SAMP>, and press
<KBD>Enter</KBD>.  This will adjust the data from the
receivers for later processing.  At the bottom of the screen, the
operator may now make the following changes, if necessary:<P>

<DL>
<DD>a. Change the antenna height, if necessary, by pressing
<KBD>F3</KBD> and entering the correct antenna height.  This will not
need to be changed if the correct height was entered into the base
station when measurements began.

<DD>b. Change the radius from <SAMP>0.0000</SAMP> to
<SAMP>0.1150</SAMP>.

<DD>c. Go to the DOS shell by pressing <KBD>F1</KBD>.

<DD>d. Select the changes by pressing <KBD>F10</KBD>, or
<KBD>Enter</KBD>.

<DD>e. Quitting the program by pressing <KBD>Esc</KBD>.
</DL>

<LI>After pressing the <KBD>F10</KBD> key to save selections,
the pop-up screen will disappear.<P>

<LI>To change the coordinates on the base station data, highlight the
file title, press <KBD>Enter</KBD>, and enter the correct
coordinates.  Then press <KBD>F10</KBD> to save the changes.
After pressing <KBD>F10</KBD>, you will automatically return
to the <SAMP>Program Options</SAMP> menu.<P>

<STRONG>NOTE:  This change is not required if the correct position was
entered into the base station (Screen 4) before measurements
began.</STRONG><P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="IMAGES/IMAGE21.JPG"></CENTER><P>

<LI>Tab to the <SAMP>B) Apply Corrections</SAMP> option and press
<KBD>Enter</KBD>.  This will display all files (designated as
<SAMP>B-files</SAMP>) and allow the operator to specify which files are
to be processed.  All files or an individual file can be specified,
with the exception of the fixed site file.<P>

<STRONG>NOTE: The determination of the decision in Step 6.4.6 to 6.4.9
and 6.4.12 shall be based on direction from the responsible Project
Manager or any procedure addressing collection of this
data.</STRONG><P>

<LI>If only an individual file is desired to be corrected, tab to that
file and press <KBD>Enter</KBD> or
<KBD>F10</KBD>.<P>

<LI>If differential corrections are to be made to all files, tab to
<SAMP>ALL B-FILES</SAMP>, and press <KBD>F10</KBD> to
accept.  You must then deselect files that you do not want to process
by tabbing to that file and pressing the <KBD>Del</KBD> key.
An <SAMP>X</SAMP> will appear next to each file you deselect.<P>

<LI>To re-select a file, tab to that file and press the
<KBD>Insert</KBD> key.<P>

<LI>After all desired files have been deselected, tab to the <SAMP>ALL
B-FILES</SAMP> option, and press the <KBD>Enter</KBD> or
<KBD>F10</KBD> key.<P>

<LI>A query will appear asking the following:<P>

<SAMP>DO YOU WANT TO AVERAGE STATIC SITES? (Y/N)</SAMP><P>

<LI>If the operator chose an individual site only, press
<KBD>N</KBD>.<P>

<LI>If several or all sites were chosen, the operator can choose either
<KBD>Y</KBD> or <KBD>N</KBD>.  By choosing yes, a
<CODE>VECTORS.OUT</CODE> file with the averaged positions, is
created.<P>

<LI>To view the corrected positions, return to DOS and type the
directory and file name the B-files were output to.<P>
</OL>

