<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Operating Ashtech ME-XII GPS Receivers Using
Real-time Differential Corrections Broadcast via UHF
Radios</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="IMAGES/YWEAVE.GIF">
<BASEFONT SIZE="4">
<CENTER><H1>Operating Ashtech ME-XII GPS Receivers Using Real-time Differential
Corrections Broadcast via UHF Radios</H1></CENTER>

<H2>Base Station Setup</H2>

<OL>
<LI> Connect Radio to ME-XII receiver using the serial cable with the
radio (gray cable). Use Port A on the ME-XII.<P>

<LI> Connect Power and antennas to radio and GPS receiver. (antennas
must be connected to the radio before powering up) Turn on radio and
GPS receiver.<P>

<LI> Press <KBD>4</KBD> on the GPS receiver finger pad.  Press the
<KBD>e</KBD> key to start enter mode and move the blinking cursor to
the first item after <SAMP>POS</SAMP>.  Enter the coordinates for the
base station.  For McKinney Ridge it is:<P>

<DL>
<DD><KBD>35 56.54063   84 22.90383    281.0205</KBD><P>
</DL>

Hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key again when finished entering the
coordinates.<P>

<LI> Hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key and move the cursor to the words
<SAMP>PORT A SETUP</SAMP>.  Highlight the <SAMP>BAUD RATE</SAMP> and
toggle it so it reads <SAMP>9600</SAMP>, and hit the <KBD>e</KBD>
key.<P>

<LI> Hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key and move the cursor to the word
<SAMP>DIFFERENTIAL</SAMP> and hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key again.  The word
<SAMP>DISABLED</SAMP>, <SAMP>REMOTE</SAMP>, or <SAMP>BASE</SAMP> will
be hightlighted.  Toggle using the <KBD>9</KBD> key until the word
<SAMP>BASE</SAMP> shows.  Then press the down arrow key once and toggle
through with the <KBD>9</KBD> so the words <SAMP>USE PORT A</SAMP>
shows.  Press the down arrow key again to get to <SAMP>ASHTECH
FORMAT</SAMP> or <SAMP>RTCM</SAMP>:  toggle with the <KBD>9</KBD> key
until the <SAMP>RTCM</SAMP> shows.  With <SAMP>RTCM</SAMP> highlighted
press <KBD>1</KBD>.  Toggle the mode field until it says
<SAMP>BASE</SAMP>. Move to the <SAMP>SPD</SAMP> field and toggle until
<SAMP>300</SAMP> appears.  Move to the <SAMP>STID</SAMP> field and make
sure <SAMP>0000</SAMP> appears.  Move to the <SAMP>TYPE 6</SAMP> field
and toggle it so it is <SAMP>OFF</SAMP>. Go to <SAMP>FRQ</SAMP> and set
it to <SAMP>001</SAMP>.<P>

<LI> Hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key until you are back to Screen 4 and press
<KBD>5</KBD> to go to screen 5.  If the receiver is calculating
corrections you will see numbers in each of the fields.<P>

</OL>

<H2>Remote Receiver Setup</H2>

<OL>
<LI> Connect Radio to ME-XII receiver using the serial cable with the
radio (gray cable). Use Port A on the ME-XII.<P>

<LI> Connect Power and antennas to radio and GPS receiver.  Antennas
must be connected to the radio before powering up.  Turn on radio and
GPS receiver.<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="IMAGES/IMAGE15.JPG"></CENTER><P>

<LI> Hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key and move the cursor to the words
<SAMP>PORT A SETUP</SAMP>.  Highlight the <SAMP>BAUD RATE</SAMP> and
toggle it so it reads <SAMP>9600</SAMP>, and hit the <KBD>e</KBD>
key.<P>

<LI> Press <KBD>4</KBD> on the GPS receiver finger pad.  Press the
<KBD>e</KBD> key to start enter mode and move the blinking cursor to
the word <SAMP>DIFFERENTIAL</SAMP> and hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key again.
The word <SAMP>DISABLED</SAMP>, <SAMP>REMOTE</SAMP>, or
<SAMP>BASE</SAMP> with be hightlighted.  Toggle using the <KBD>9</KBD>
key until the word <SAMP>REMOTE</SAMP> shows.  Then press the down
arrow key once and toggle through with the <KBD>9</KBD> so the words
<SAMP>USE PORT A</SAMP> shows.  Press the down arrow key again to get
to <SAMP>ASHTECH FORMAT</SAMP> or <SAMP>RTCM</SAMP>: toggle with the
<KBD>9</KBD> key until the <SAMP>RTCM</SAMP> shows.  With the
<SAMP>RTCM</SAMP> highlighted press <KBD>1</KBD>.  Toggle the
<SAMP>MODE</SAMP> field until it says <SAMP>REMOTE</SAMP>. Move to the
<SAMP>SPD</SAMP> field and toggle until <SAMP>300</SAMP> appears.  Move
to the <SAMP>STID</SAMP> field and make sure <SAMP>0000</SAMP>
appears.  Move to the <SAMP>TYPE 6</SAMP> field and toggle it so it is
<SAMP>OFF</SAMP>. Go to <SAMP>FRQ</SAMP> and set it to
<SAMP>001</SAMP>.<P>

<LI> Hit the <KBD>e</KBD> key until you are back to Screen 4 and press
<KBD>5</KBD> to go to screen 5.  If the receiver is receiving
corrections you will see numbers in each of the fields.  Go to screen
2, the corrected data will appear here.<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="IMAGES/IMAGE21.JPG"></CENTER><P>

</OL>

<HR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="INDEX.HTM">ESD Global Positioning System (GPS)</A> /
<A HREF="http://www.esd.ornl.gov/~forrest">webmaster@www.esd.ornl.gov</A>
