<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Downloading Data Files from Ashtech GPS
Receivers</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="IMAGES/YWEAVE.GIF">
<BASEFONT SIZE="4">
<CENTER><H1>Downloading Data Files from Ashtech GPS Receivers</H1></CENTER>

<OL>
<LI>Each project must have it's own sub-directory on the computer hard
drive.  It is advisable to have sub-directories within each project
directory as well to keep data collected from each day separate. Use
DOS commands to make data directories:<P>

<DL>
<DD> a. From the <SAMP>C:\</SAMP> prompt type <KBD>mkdir project</KBD>
to make a directory named <SAMP>project</SAMP>.

<DD> b. Type <KBD>cd project</KBD> to change to the new directory.

<DD> c. Type <KBD>mkdir </KBD><VAR>mmmdd</VAR> (e.g. <KBD>NOV22</KBD>)
to make a sub-directory for the month and day of data collection you
are processing.

<DD> d. Type <KBD>cd </KBD><VAR>mmmdd</VAR> to change to the new
directory.  Everything you do during this session will be saved in this
directory.  </DL><P>

<LI> Connect the full-handshake null-modem cable to the computer.  One
end of the cable plugs into the computer's RS-232 serial port (COM1 or
COM2).  The other end plugs into the receiver's RS-232 serial ports.
The ME-XII model receivers have a different plug than the Ranger model
receiver.<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="IMAGES/IMAGE26.JPG"></CENTER><P>

<LI> Connect receiver to power supply and turn it on.<P>

<LI> On the computer, change to the project directory and type
<KBD>RANGER</KBD> or <KBD>GPPS</KBD> depending on which software you
are using.<P>

<LI> If you typed <SAMP>RANGER</SAMP> in step 3 select <SAMP>A)
Download Receiver</SAMP> from the menu by either typing the
<KBD>A</KBD> key, or using the arrow keys to highlight and press
<KBD>Enter</KBD>.  If you typed <SAMP>GPPS</SAMP> in step 3 select
<SAMP>B) Download Receiver</SAMP> from the menu.<P>

<STRONG>NOTE:  The <SAMP>HOSE</SAMP> Program will communicate through
COM1 at 38,400 baud.  If this differs with the computer, the
<SAMP>HOSE</SAMP> program will display the following error message:</STRONG><P>
<DL>
<DD><SAMP>ERROR: Cannot initialize COM port</SAMP>
</DL><P>

<LI> To correct problems with port or baud rate, tab to <SAMP>C) Change
communication parameters</SAMP>.<P>

<DL>
<DD> a. Press <KBD>Enter</KBD> to select.
<DD> b. Tab down to <SAMP>COM1 COM2</SAMP> selection and select
<SAMP>COM2</SAMP> and press <KBD>Enter</KBD> or the <KBD>F10</KBD>
key.
<DD> c. You can change any of the communication parameters you need to
at this point.
</DL>

<STRONG>NOTE:  If power is terminated to the receiver while
<SAMP>HOSE</SAMP> is running, the program will have to be
restarted.</STRONG><P>

<LI> Downloading data to a different drive can be accomplished as follows:<P>

<DL>
<DD> a. Return to Main Options Menu by pressing <KBD>Esc</KBD>.
<DD> b. Press <KBD>D</KBD>, or tab down to <SAMP>D) Change destination
path</SAMP> and press <KBD>Enter</KBD>.
<DD> c. Enter the desired drive and directory path and press the
<KBD>F10</KBD> key, or <KBD>Enter</KBD>.
</DL><P>

<LI> Return to Main options Menu by pressing <KBD>Esc</KBD>.<P>

<LI> Press <KBD>B</KBD>, or tab to <SAMP>B) Download receiver
files</SAMP> and press <KBD>Enter</KBD> to start the downloading of
data process.<P>

<LI> A list of files on the receiver will appear.  Since the receiver
will store up to eight files at a time there may be some files left
that are not part of your project. You can choose not to load them by
tabbing down to the <SAMP>Y</SAMP> at the left of each file name you
don't want and replacing it with an <SAMP>N</SAMP>.<P>

<STRONG>NOTE: You can also change file names here.  For instance, if
you named two sites identically in the field or on two different
receivers you can rename one of them here so that they are processed as
being unique sites.</STRONG><P>

<LI> When you have marked all the files you want to load with a
<KBD>Y</KBD>, press the <KBD>F10</KBD> function key to start the
downloading.  The screen will display the downloading status as it
progresses and report any errors if the program encounters any.<P>

<LI> You'll want to download data files from other recievers.  To do
this you must reset the computer and press <KBD>E</KBD>, or tab down to
<SAMP>E) Resetting for new receiver</SAMP> and press <KBD>Enter</KBD>.
The screen will present a list of action items that will reset the
program to download a new receiver.<P>

<LI> Follow the instructions on the screen and return to step 10
above.<P>

<LI> Repeat steps 9 through 13 until all the files off of all the
receivers you want are in the same project directory.<P>

<LI> Press <KBD>Esc</KBD> to return to the main processing menu of either
<SAMP>GPPS</SAMP> or <SAMP>RANGER</SAMP>.<P>
</OL>

<HR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="INDEX.HTM">ESD Global Positioning System (GPS)</A> /
<A HREF="http://www.esd.ornl.gov/~forrest">webmaster@www.esd.ornl.gov</A>
</ADDRESS></BASEFONT></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
