<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Field Use of the Ashtech GPS Receivers</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="IMAGES/YWEAVE.GIF">
<BASEFONT SIZE="4">
<CENTER><H1>Field Use of the Ashtech GPS Receivers</H1></CENTER>

<OL>
<LI> Connect the appropriate cables for operation.<P>

<DL>
<DD> a. Attach the antenna to the stand.
<DD> b. Attach the antenna cable to the antenna and to the receiver.
<DD> c. Connect the battery cable to the battery and the receiver.
</DL><P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="IMAGES/IMAGE15.JPG"></CENTER><P>

<LI> Turn the receiver on by locating the toggle switch on the back of
the receiver, and switch to "ON."<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="IMAGES/IMAGE26.JPG"></CENTER><P>

<LI> Go to Screen 9 by pressing <KBD>9</KBD> or using the left or right
arrows.<P>

<LI> While the boat, or more specifically the antenna, is moving there
should be four question marks in the site ID space <SAMP>????</SAMP>.
Once you are stationary at the site that you want coordinates for enter
a site ID other than the four question marks.<P>

<LI> Press the <KBD>e</KBD> to enter a site ID.  A limit of four
characters can be used in this field.  The alpha-numeric keys are
displayed on the receiver screen.  The numbers 0-9, are shown first.
To get to any letter of the alphabet press the up arrow key.  By
continually pressing this key you can scroll through the alphabet and
return to the numeric keys.  Press the corresponding number to the
number or letter you want.  The down arrow key does not return you to
the previous numbers or letters.<P>

<LI> Enter the appropriate site ID and press the <KBD>e</KBD> key to
start logging data for that site.  If you make a mistake while entering
the site ID just press the <KBD>c</KBD> key and start over at step
4.<P>

<LI> Let the receiver log data for at least 3 minutes at each
location.<P>

<LI> Before the boat (or antenna) moves enter four question marks in
the site ID by following these key strokes: <KBD>e</KBD>, up arrow,
<KBD>9999</KBD>, <KBD>e</KBD>.<P>

<LI> Repeat steps 4 trough 8 for each site.<P>

<LI> When you are finished logging data, turn off the receiver.  All
the data collected is stored automatically in a file using the last
site name as the file name.<P>

</OL>

<HR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="INDEX.HTM">ESD Global Positioning System (GPS)</A> /
<A HREF="http://www.esd.ornl.gov/~forrest">webmaster@www.esd.ornl.gov</A>
