<CENTER><H1>Operation of the Ashtech ME-XII GPS Base Station</H1></CENTER>

<OL>
<LI> Before you go into the field turn the receiver on by locating the
toggle switch on the back of the receiver, and switch to "ON."<P>

<LI> Go to Screen 9 pressing <KBD>9</KBD> or using the left and right
arrows.<P>

<LI> Press the <KBD>e</KBD> to enter a site ID.  A limit of four
characters can be used in this field.  The alpha-numeric keys are
displayed on the receiver screen.  The numbers 0-9 are shown first.  To
get to any letter of the alphabet press the up arrow key.  By
continually pressing this key you can scroll through the alphabet and
return to the numeric keys.  Press the corresponding number to the
number or letter you want.  The down arrow key does not return you to
the previous numbers or letters.<P>

<LI> Enter the appropriate site ID (an abreviation of the date is
recommended) and press the <KBD>e</KBD> key to start logging data for
that site.  If you make a mistake while entering the site ID just press
the <KBD>c</KBD> key and start over at step 4.<P>

