<body>
<h1>Use of Tracers to Confirm Sources for
Contaminated Seeps</h1>
<h3>By D. D. Huff and W.E. Sanford</h3>
<h3>Oak Ridge National Laboratory,</h3>
<h3>Oak Ridge, TN 37831-6400</h3>
<hr>
<p>

<h2>Welcome!</h2>
<img src="w483.gif" alt="wag 4" align="left"><p>

<b>Waste Area Grouping (WAG) 4, shown here, currently releases about 25% of all the
radioactive strontium leaving the Oak Ridge National Laboratory complex.  The tracer
work described in this poster session helped identify the sources of release, which are
scheduled for remedial action in 1996.</b><p>

