<P>
<IMG SRC="photos/hydrofra.gif" ALT="Remedial activites at the Hydrofracture Facility">
<H3>Documenting Remedial Actions </H3>

<P>
The ability to acquire inexpensive aerial photographs makes it
easy to document remedial activities at waste sites. The above
photograph shows ongoing construction activities at the Oak Ridge
Deep Hydrofracture Injection Facility, a site active in the 1960s
where radioactive waste was mixed with concrete grout and injected
deep underground.  Photographs taken before, during, and after
remediation provide an excellent record of the clean-up. 
<P>
<IMG SRC="greenball.gif"><A HREF="signif.htm" >Significance</A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="redball.gif">Return to <A HREF="toc.htm">Table of Contents</A>
