<BODY>

<H1>Acknowledgments </H1>

<P>
We would like to acknowledge the encouragement and guidance provided by Jim Walker, a pioneer of using radio-controlled aircraft for aerial photography; Jim and his students built the first two planes we tested. Jerel Zarestky, and avid radio-control hobbyist, deserves credit as test pilot of many of our aircraft. John Smyre, a scientist in the ORNL Computer Applications Development Section has assisted with GIS applications and image rectification. 
We would also like to thank Dale Huff and Tom Early of the Oak Ridge Groundwater Program Office for providing the start-up funds to begin this work. The bulk of the funding for this project, however, has come from the DOE Office of Technology Development (OTD). Our OTD project facilitator, Bryan Albers has encouraged our work and made many useful suggestions.  
<p>
This work was performed at Oak Ridge National Laboratory, managed by Lockheed Martin Energy Research Corp. for the U.S. Department of Energy under contract number DE-AC05-96OR22464.

