<HEAD>
<TITLE>3rd Biomass Conference of the Americas: Announcement</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#008000">
<P><A HREF="../index.html"><IMG
SRC="../images/bintiny.gif" ALT="BIN logo" ALIGN="RIGHT"></A><A
HREF="../bfdpmain.html"><IMG
SRC="../images/bfdptiny.gif" ALT="BFDP logo" ALIGN="RIGHT"></A></P>
<CENTER>
<H1><I>Third Biomass Conference of the Americas: Making a Business from
Biomass in Energy, Environment, Chemicals, Fibers and Materials</I></H1>
<H2>First Announcement and Call for Papers</H2>
<H3><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">August 24-29, 1997<BR>Sheraton Center<BR>Montr&eacute;al,
Qu&eacute;bec, Canada</FONT></H3></CENTER>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Background and Scope:</FONT></H2>
<P>The Third Biomass Conference of the Americas will provide an international
forum in support of the development of a viable biomass-based industry.  The
focus will be on applications of biomass (plantations, crops, residues, wastes).
 The emphasis will be on how to make a profitable business from biomass within a
vision of sustainabilitv.  The conference will discuss technology transfer,
scale up demonstrations, commercial realizations, arid business development for
biomass-based industries.  As well, the conference will be a forum to evaluate
novel science and technology (processes and products. Attendees will have the
opportunity to evaluate biomass programs and projects from all over the world.</P>
